Alembic migrations (async).

The database URL and engine come from app.core.config / app.db.session — do not
put credentials in alembic.ini.

Common commands (run from backend/, with the venv active and .env filled in):

  alembic upgrade head                      # apply all migrations
  alembic revision -m "add interns tables"  # hand-write a migration
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "..."  # diff models vs DB (review output!)
  alembic downgrade -1                       # roll back one

Gotcha (PLAN §13.4): adding values to an existing ENUM (e.g. user_role) cannot
run inside a transaction — use an AUTOCOMMIT block in that migration.
